long_desc.thetext:
Take a look at the following demo code:


var f = new qx.ui.embed.Iframe();
f.setSource("http://demo.qooxdoo.org");
this.getRoot().add(f, {edge: 0});
qx.ui.core.queue.Manager.flush();

window.setTimeout(function() {
  f.setSource("http://qooxdoo.org");
  var win = new qx.ui.window.Window();
  win.setLayout(new qx.ui.layout.Canvas());
  win.add(f);
  win.open();
}, 1000);




First, a iframe is added and a url is set (demos page). After a second, we change the url and change the position in the DOM --> the url is not applied. I debugged it down to line 181 in qx.bom.Iframe which uses location.replace instead of assign [1] or the source attribute. Unfortunately, this causes Firefox to break and not apply the new source.

[1] https://developer.mozilla.org/en/DOM/window.location
